<hl>
<seg id=1> Russian Premier on Russian Economy </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Moscow. Jan. 8.  Russian Premier Chernomerkin said in a state conference held on 8 that Russian's main achievement in 1997 was that it has created basic preconditions for future economic growth. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to Russian News Agency -- Tass News Agency. Chernomerkin said, compared with 1996,Russian's GDP of 1997 increased by 1.2%, the output of industry was up 3.2%, the total retail sales of goods up 3.9%,the annual inflation rate was 11%,half of the rate of 1996,urban residents' income rose by 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Chernomerkin at the same time pointed out that last year there remained quite a few problems domestically such as poor revenue, unfulfilled investment schemes, diminishing trade surplus and the government's ineffective financial measures. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Referring to this year's work, Chernomerkin said a new program to promote structural reform and economic growth was under drafting, which will be submitted to the February 26 extended state conference for discussion. </seg>
<seg id=6> According to this program, Russian's GDP of next year is to make an increase of 2%, while the inflation rate should be reduced to the range from 5% to 8%. </seg>
</p>
